When this file is evaluated and no arguments are passed to DPP, the following
is displayed.

$ dpp < non-optional-arguments
/home/dylan/bin/dpp: eval: line 21: 1: usage: dpp [title] [author]

$ dpp "My Blog Post" < non-optional-arguments
/home/dylan/bin/dpp: eval: line 22: 1: usage: dpp [title] [author]

$ dpp "My Blog Post" "Dylan Araps" < non-optional-arguments

# My Blog Post

Written by Dylan Araps.

...

